org.qcri.rheem.core.plan.executionplan

Interface ChannelInitializer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BroadcastChannel.Initializer, CollectionChannel.Initializer, FileChannels.Initializer, HdfsFileInitializer, HdfsFileInitializer, StreamChannel.Initializer

    public interface ChannelInitializer
    Sets up the usage of Channel in an ExecutionPlan for a given Platform.

    • Method Detail

      • setUpOutput

        Channel setUpOutput(ChannelDescriptor descriptor,
                    ExecutionTask executionTask,
                    int index)
        Optional operation. Implements the Channel on the index-th output of the given ExecutionTask, thereby adding potentially further ExecutionTasks required for using the Channel. However, if it encounters already set-up Channels, the implementation is free to reuse them if appropriate or even necessary.
        Parameters:
        descriptor - describes the Channel to be created
        executionTask - that should output to the new Channel
        index - the output index of the executionTask that should feed the Channel
        Returns:
        the newly created and set-up or reused Channel

      • setUpInput

        void setUpInput(Channel channel,
                ExecutionTask executionTask,
                int index)
        Optional operation. Implements the Channel on the index-th output of the given ExecutionTask, thereby adding potentially further ExecutionTasks required for using the Channel. It may reuse existing ExecutionTasks and Channels when appropriate or necessary.
        Parameters:
        channel - the Channel to be consumed as input
        executionTask - that should output to the new Channel
        index - the output index of the executionTask that should feed the Channel
